        <div class="about-kicker">Systems operator first. Product finisher by habit.</div>
        <p class="atp">I'm the <strong>Senior Technical Support Manager</strong> at <strong>Maven Imaging</strong> &mdash; where I&rsquo;ve architected 10+ PACS migrations (including a million-file Candelis legacy transfer when vendor tooling gave up), restored 54 customer cloud accounts through a cross-vendor transition, and support medical imaging clinics across the Caribbean, East Africa, and East Asia. Before this I spent 11 years as Systems Administrator at <strong>ThinkTV</strong> (PBS affiliate) running Windows servers, Cisco networking, Hyper-V, and SCCM, with four years at a Dayton MSP before that.</p>
        <p class="atp">When a vendor tool fails at the worst possible moment, I write the replacement. That habit has produced a full set of in-house utilities &mdash; a custom DICOM C-Store sender, a PC-provisioning kit, an acquisition-PC network scanner, a service-watcher script that keeps overnight transfers alive &mdash; on top of the <strong id="aboutReposText">{stats.totalRepos}+</strong> <strong>public projects</strong> on GitHub across PowerShell, Python, JavaScript, Kotlin, C#, and C++. Several of them (DICOM PACS Migrator, RadAtlas, Generator Specs) went from side-project to company-wide production tools.</p>
